CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 1, 1945, pg. 24 reads: "Kiddie Party - A birthday party was given recently for Dian Ilona Walker, three-year-old daughter of Pfc. and Mrs. James C. Walker, at 268 Paulson Avenue. Guests were Marian Baker, John Baker, Arbutus, Patricia and Quintella Cathie; Barbara and Audrey Ficklin, Helene Fisher, Diana Blackwell, Henry Walker Jr., Patricia Anderson, Lloyd Thornton, William Page Jr., Donna Strayhorn, Barbara Jean Saunders, Madeline Formley, Joyce Walker, Bobby and Billy Cogdall, and Sonny and Jean Weatherly. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of birthday party, including Marian Baker, John Baker, Patricia Cathie, Quintella Cathie, Barbara Ficklin, Audrey Ficklin, Helene Fisher, Diana Blackwell, Henry Walker Jr., Patricia Anderson, Lloyd Thornton, William Page Jr., Donna Strayhorn, Barbara Jean Saunders, Madelin Formley, Joyce Walker, Bobby Cogdall, Billy Cogdall, Sonny Weatherly, and Jean Weatherly, surrounding Dian Ilona Walker standing behind her birthday cake including girl wearing gingham dress with light colored collar, gathered around birthday cake, posed in home of Pfc. and Mrs. James C. Walker, 268 Paulson Avenue
